<div class="wiki-item">
	<h3 class="title"><a class="" href="/wiki/777/clear-cgridview-filters-sort-pager/">Clear CGridView Filters, Sort &amp; Pager</a></h3>
    <div class="teaser">
        <div class="info">
                        Created about a month ago            by <a class="g-user-rank-link silver" href="/user/5458/">le_top</a>                                &ndash; <a href="/wiki/?category=2">How-tos</a>            		&ndash; <a href="/wiki/777/clear-cgridview-filters-sort-pager/#comments">0 comments</a>    		&ndash; viewed 2,653 times
                    &ndash;
            ( <span class="g-vote plus" title="1 votes up">+1</span> )
                            &ndash;
            version <strong>1.1</strong>
                </div>
        Clearing CGridView filters and sort orders from the web pages, is usefull for the end user.  Yii does not seem to propose a standard method.  Furthermore, this is especially usefull when filters are &quot;remembered&quot; in the user&#039;s session.                    <div class="tags">
                <strong>tags:</strong>
                <a href="/wiki/?tag=CGridView">CGridView</a>, <a href="/wiki/?tag=filter">filter</a>, <a href="/wiki/?tag=filters">filters</a>, <a href="/wiki/?tag=filtering">filtering</a>, <a href="/wiki/?tag=clear+filters">clear filters</a>, <a href="/wiki/?tag=clear">clear</a>, <a href="/wiki/?tag=gridview">gridview</a>, <a href="/wiki/?tag=reset">reset</a>, <a href="/wiki/?tag=remember">remember</a>            </div>
        		<div class="clear"></div>
	</div>
</div>
<div class="wiki-item">
	<h3 class="title"><a class="" href="/wiki/776/how-to-keep-filters-simple-in-cgridview/">How to keep filters simple in CGridView</a></h3>
    <div class="teaser">
        <div class="info">
                        Created about a month ago            by <a class="g-user-rank-link" href="/user/102362/">Peppe</a>                                &ndash; <a href="/wiki/?category=2">How-tos</a>            		&ndash; <a href="/wiki/776/how-to-keep-filters-simple-in-cgridview/#comments">2 comments</a>    		&ndash; viewed 1,934 times
                            &ndash;
            version <strong>1.1</strong>
                </div>
        The problem is not new: after setting some filters in a grid (typically in admin view), and gone to another page, returning in the grid&#039;s page I would like to find the filters with previous setting mantained.                    <div class="tags">
                <strong>tags:</strong>
                <a href="/wiki/?tag=CGridView">CGridView</a>, <a href="/wiki/?tag=filtering">filtering</a>            </div>
        		<div class="clear"></div>
	</div>
</div>
<div class="wiki-item">
	<h3 class="title"><a class="" href="/wiki/653/displaying-sorting-and-filtering-model-relations-on-a-gridview/">Displaying, Sorting and Filtering Model Relations on a GridView</a></h3>
    <div class="teaser">
        <div class="info">
                        Created 8 months ago            by <a class="g-user-rank-link gold" href="/user/7106/">Antonio Ramirez</a>                                &ndash; <a href="/wiki/?category=2">How-tos</a>            		&ndash; <a href="/wiki/653/displaying-sorting-and-filtering-model-relations-on-a-gridview/#comments">2 comments</a>    		&ndash; viewed 9,915 times
                    &ndash;
            ( <span class="g-vote plus" title="10 votes up">+10</span> )
                            &ndash;
            version <strong>2.0</strong>
                </div>
        One of the things you will find tricky to implement is the the sorting and filtering of a GridView&#039;s column that displays related model data.                    <div class="tags">
                <strong>tags:</strong>
                <a href="/wiki/?tag=yii2">yii2</a>, <a href="/wiki/?tag=gridview">gridview</a>, <a href="/wiki/?tag=sorting">sorting</a>, <a href="/wiki/?tag=filtering">filtering</a>            </div>
        		<div class="clear"></div>
	</div>
</div>
<div class="wiki-item">
	<h3 class="title"><a class="" href="/wiki/385/displaying-sorting-and-filtering-hasmany-manymany-relations-in-cgridview/">Displaying, sorting and filtering HasMany &amp; ManyMany relations in CGridView</a></h3>
    <div class="teaser">
        <div class="info">
                        Created 2 years ago            by <a class="g-user-rank-link" href="/user/39877/">yJeroen</a>                                &ndash; <a href="/wiki/?category=3">Tutorials</a>            		&ndash; <a href="/wiki/385/displaying-sorting-and-filtering-hasmany-manymany-relations-in-cgridview/#comments">8 comments</a>    		&ndash; viewed 44,538 times
                    &ndash;
            ( <span class="g-vote plus" title="19 votes up">+19</span> )
                            &ndash;
            version <strong>1.1</strong>
                </div>
        This tutorial gives you multiple options of how to fully implement showing, sorting and filtering related data in gridviews.                    <div class="tags">
